<frame name="Be_in_agreement_on_assessment" ID="1496" xsi:schemaLocation="../schema/frame.xsd" xmlns="http://framenet.icsi.berkeley.edu" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" domains="Cognitive_positions">
    <definition>&lt;def-root&gt;The &lt;fen&gt;Cognizers&lt;/fen&gt; have a similarity (or dissimilarity) in their &lt;fen&gt;Opinion&lt;/fen&gt;. The &lt;fen&gt;Cognizers&lt;/fen&gt; may be expressed separately, with &lt;fen&gt;Cognizer_2&lt;/fen&gt; being the basis for establishing the &lt;fen&gt;Opinion&lt;/fen&gt; of &lt;fen&gt;Cognizer_1&lt;/fen&gt;.  Rather than a specific &lt;fen&gt;Opinion&lt;/fen&gt;, a phenomenon about which a similar or differing &lt;fen&gt;Opinion&lt;/fen&gt; is held, the &lt;fen&gt;Topic&lt;/fen&gt;, may be specified. 
<!-- A specific &lt;fen&gt;Opinion&lt;/fen&gt; may also go unmentioned when the &lt;fen&gt;Opinion&lt;/fen&gt;s of the &lt;fen&gt;Cognizers&lt;/fen&gt; are understood as answers to a &lt;fen&gt;Question&lt;/fen&gt;.

&lt;ex&gt;&lt;fex name="Cognizers"&gt;Dr. Gerry and Mr. Pond&lt;/fex&gt; &lt;t&gt;agree&lt;/t&gt; &lt;fex name="Question"&gt;in their impressions&lt;/fex&gt;.&lt;/ex&gt;
-->

&lt;ex&gt; &lt;fex name="Cognizers"&gt;This copyeditor and I&lt;/fex&gt; &lt;fex name="Degree"&gt;mostly&lt;/fex&gt; &lt;t&gt;see&lt;/t&gt; &lt;t&gt;eye&lt;/t&gt; &lt;t&gt;to&lt;/t&gt; &lt;t&gt;eye&lt;/t&gt; &lt;fex name="Topic"&gt;on things&lt;/fex&gt;.&lt;/ex&gt;

&lt;ex&gt;&lt;fex name="Cognizer_1"&gt;I&lt;/fex&gt; &lt;t&gt;agree&lt;/t&gt; &lt;fex name="cog2"&gt;with you&lt;/fex&gt; &lt;fex name="Opinion"&gt;that everything should be monitored to keep the person from wasting time and protecting the interests of the company&lt;/fex&gt;.&lt;/ex&gt;

&lt;ex&gt;&lt;/ex&gt;
Distinctions with other frames:
&lt;ex&gt;&lt;/ex&gt;

    ≠ &lt;frframe&gt;FR_Make_agreement_on_assessment&lt;/frframe&gt;: FR_Make_agreement_on_assessment is inchoative of Be_in_agreement_on_assessment.


 &lt;ex&gt; &lt;/ex&gt;
    ≠ &lt;frframe&gt;Be_in_agreement_on_action&lt;/frframe&gt;: Be_in_agreement_on_assessment is about Cognizers having a similar opinion (about some content, the Topic) whereas Be_in_agreement_on_action is about Parties having an agreement binding them to an Obligation.

&lt;ex&gt;&lt;/ex&gt;

&lt;asf&gt;ASFALDA French FrameNet comment&lt;/asf&gt;: 
&lt;ex&gt;&lt;/ex&gt;
We do not use the Question FE which is difficult to distinguish from the Topic FE.

&lt;/def-root&gt;</definition>
    <FE bgColor="FF0000" fgColor="FFFFFF" coreType="Core" cBy="605" cDate="06/16/2005 05:14:07 PDT Thu" abbrev="cogs" name="Cognizers" ID="8177">
        <definition>&lt;def-root&gt;This FE marks constituents that express the set of &lt;fen&gt;Cognizers&lt;/fen&gt; whose similarity of opinion is at issue. 

&lt;/def-root&gt;</definition>
        <excludesFE name="Cognizer_1" ID="8178"/>
    </FE>
    <FE bgColor="0000FF" fgColor="FFFFFF" coreType="Core" cBy="605" cDate="06/16/2005 05:14:08 PDT Thu" abbrev="cog1" name="Cognizer_1" ID="8178">
        <definition>&lt;def-root&gt;When there is an asymmetry, &lt;fen&gt;Cognizer_1&lt;/fen&gt; is the individual characterized by their similarity in opinion to &lt;fen&gt;Cognizer_2&lt;/fen&gt;, whose opinion is assumed to be known.  &lt;fen&gt;Cognizer_1&lt;/fen&gt; is often an external argument.
&lt;/def-root&gt;</definition>
        <requiresFE name="Cognizer_2" ID="8179"/>
        <excludesFE name="Cognizers" ID="8177"/>
    </FE>
    <FE bgColor="008000" fgColor="FFFFFF" coreType="Core" cBy="605" cDate="06/16/2005 05:14:08 PDT Thu" abbrev="cog2" name="Cognizer_2" ID="8179">
        <definition>&lt;def-root&gt;When the &lt;fen&gt;Cognizers&lt;/fen&gt; are expressed separately, &lt;fen&gt;Cognizer_2&lt;/fen&gt; is the one whose opinion is assumed to be known; it serves as a basis for establishing the opinion of &lt;fen&gt;Cognizer_1&lt;/fen&gt;.
&lt;/def-root&gt;</definition>
        <requiresFE name="Cognizer_1" ID="8178"/>
        <excludesFE name="Cognizers" ID="8177"/>
    </FE>
